14
00:00:52,987 --> 00:00:57,389
      fencing is one of the     
  oldest forms of armed combat. 

15
00:00:57,391 --> 00:01:01,427
    in the late 18th century,   
  fencing evolved into a sport. 

16
00:01:01,429 --> 00:01:03,596
  as fencing gained popularity, 

17
00:01:03,598 --> 00:01:05,864
 a steel mesh mask was invented 

18
00:01:05,866 --> 00:01:08,968
  to protect the eyes and face  
          from injury.          

19
00:01:13,274 --> 00:01:17,543
 before fencers say "en garde," 
     they don a face guard.     

20
00:01:17,545 --> 00:01:21,614
  today, fencing is recognized  
      as an olympic sport,      

21
00:01:21,616 --> 00:01:25,684
    so special mesh masks are   
      required to compete.      

22
00:01:25,686 --> 00:01:28,087
    regulation fencing masks    
            are made            

23
00:01:28,089 --> 00:01:31,690
     from rectangular pieces    
      of tight steel mesh.      

24
00:01:31,692 --> 00:01:34,226
        a machinist uses        
       a guillotine blade       

25
00:01:34,228 --> 00:01:38,497
      to cut the corners of     
   the mesh piece on an angle.  

26
00:01:38,499 --> 00:01:41,300
        then he transfers       
       the mesh to a press      

27
00:01:41,302 --> 00:01:44,103
    with a large mold that's    
       shaped like a face.      

28
00:01:44,105 --> 00:01:47,439
    the hydraulically powered   
      mold press bears down     

29
00:01:47,441 --> 00:01:50,876
  on the steel mesh and forces  
    it into a rounded shape.    

30
00:01:52,313 --> 00:01:55,781
      using a special tool,     
 the machinist bends steel wire 

31
00:01:55,783 --> 00:01:57,016
           to a form.           

32
00:01:59,253 --> 00:02:03,155
 he brings the ends of the wire 
   together to close the loop.  

33
00:02:04,325 --> 00:02:06,759
       an automated welder      
         fuses the ends.        

34
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:12,531
the machinist transfers the hoop
       to the next fixture      

35
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:16,135
     and places the rounded     
 steel mesh on top of the hoop. 

36
00:02:17,471 --> 00:02:21,407
        a frame descends,       
 affixing the mesh to the hoop. 

37
00:02:21,409 --> 00:02:24,276
   then multiple welding guns   
       spot-weld the mesh       

38
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:26,345
          to the hoop.          

39
00:02:26,347 --> 00:02:30,816
   a large welding gun closes   
the gaps between the spot-welds.

40
00:02:30,818 --> 00:02:32,017
           once fused,          

41
00:02:32,019 --> 00:02:34,553
 the hoop will prevent the mesh 
          from fraying          

42
00:02:34,555 --> 00:02:36,756
  and add structural rigidity.  

43
00:02:40,361 --> 00:02:41,827
      using a nibbler tool,     

44
00:02:41,829 --> 00:02:43,429
  the machinist trims the mesh, 

45
00:02:43,431 --> 00:02:45,698
     revealing a clean edge.    

46
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:48,700
   next, the technician works   
    on the mask's side piece    

47
00:02:48,702 --> 00:02:51,370
      by bending steel wire     
        into a rectangle.       

48
00:02:53,241 --> 00:02:56,509
    he places the rectangular   
       frame in a fixture       

49
00:02:56,511 --> 00:02:59,078
    and sets a piece of mesh    
         over the frame.        

50
00:03:02,383 --> 00:03:05,517
          he spot-welds         
     the mesh to the frame.     

51
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:08,120
       this step provides       
     a more consistent weld     

52
00:03:08,122 --> 00:03:09,855
     around the entire mask.    

53
00:03:12,393 --> 00:03:16,729
   copper welding wheels fuse   
 and seal the mesh to the frame.

54
00:03:16,731 --> 00:03:19,931
                     ♪          

55
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:22,268
     then the machinist uses    
        a grinding wheel        

56
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:26,472
    to remove any sharp bits    
         or protrusions.        

57
00:03:26,474 --> 00:03:27,973
       this is the result.      

58
00:03:31,012 --> 00:03:33,012
a bending device rounds the part

59
00:03:33,014 --> 00:03:36,415
     so that it will fit to     
 the sides and top of the head. 

60
00:03:37,017 --> 00:03:40,286
  he welds the rounded part to  
  the back of the fencing mask. 

61
00:03:43,024 --> 00:03:46,692
       a large welding gun      
spot-welds the assembly together

62
00:03:46,694 --> 00:03:48,961
in preparation for a final weld.

63
00:03:48,963 --> 00:03:55,300
                     ♪          

64
00:03:55,302 --> 00:03:58,971
  once complete, the machinist  
     makes a full seam weld,    

65
00:03:58,973 --> 00:04:00,572
        closing all gaps.       

66
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:03,642
    this will prevent a sword   
 from piercing through the mask,

67
00:04:03,644 --> 00:04:07,179
potentially wounding the wearer.

68
00:04:07,181 --> 00:04:10,316
      next, the technician      
 pounds out any remaining dents 

69
00:04:10,318 --> 00:04:12,384
         with a hammer,         
       restoring the mask       

70
00:04:12,386 --> 00:04:14,186
    to the desired contours.    

71
00:04:17,124 --> 00:04:20,192
   he places the fencing mask   
        on a rounded post       

72
00:04:20,194 --> 00:04:23,061
    and uses a plastic mallet   
       to hammer the mask       

73
00:04:23,063 --> 00:04:24,596
        against the post.       

74
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:28,868
     this step will improve     
 the overall shape of the mask. 

75
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:32,538
     they big is made out of    
  high molecular polyethylene,  

76
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:35,875
         which is strong        
   and extremely light weight.  

77
00:04:35,877 --> 00:04:37,943
        the bib includes        
       a thick rubber band      

78
00:04:37,945 --> 00:04:39,845
 that attaches to the mesh mask.

79
00:04:41,215 --> 00:04:43,549
          once the mesh         
     is coated with plastic,    

80
00:04:43,551 --> 00:04:45,684
   another technician installs  
           rubber trim          

81
00:04:45,686 --> 00:04:48,286
       along the perimeter      
          of the mask.          

82
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:49,922
       the plastic coating      
           on the mesh          

83
00:04:49,924 --> 00:04:53,425
 insulates the mask, preventing 
     electrical interference    

84
00:04:53,427 --> 00:04:55,394
        from the scoring        
        system's wiring.        

85
00:04:57,097 --> 00:05:00,366
 the technician pipes epoxy glue
         around the mask        

86
00:05:00,368 --> 00:05:02,902
   just above the rubber trim.  

87
00:05:02,904 --> 00:05:05,838
       he pulls the bib's       
    rubber band over the mask   

88
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,973
  and down to the bead of glue  
         at the bottom.         

89
00:05:12,046 --> 00:05:13,979
 he tucks the pieces of material

90
00:05:13,981 --> 00:05:16,648
         under the band         
       for a neater look.       

91
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:18,517
       as the glue cures,       

92
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:21,554
      the bib's rubber band     
  adheres to the fencing mask.  

93
00:05:24,124 --> 00:05:26,058
        another machinist       
       drills rivet holes       

94
00:05:26,060 --> 00:05:29,794
    through the bib and mesh    
  along the sides of the mask.  

95
00:05:29,796 --> 00:05:37,136
                     ♪          

96
00:05:37,138 --> 00:05:39,738
         then he inserts        
     and flattens the rivets    

97
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:42,041
      to pull the bib flush     
          to the mesh.          

98
00:05:44,211 --> 00:05:45,477
     each fencing discipline    

99
00:05:45,479 --> 00:05:48,814
        requires its own        
     uniquely designed mask.    

100
00:05:48,816 --> 00:05:52,484
    regardless of the design,   
each mask will allow the athlete

101
00:05:52,486 --> 00:05:55,154
   to safely enjoy the sport.   

102
